
Q.1)  is Default methods in java ?
ans : a method declares with modifire default is called as default method.

Q.2)  Default method with respect to java8 ?
ans :  Before java8 interface can contain only public abstract methods only but, from java 8 we can add static and
       default methods inside interface.

Q.3) Why we use dafault methods in interface ?
ans : Default methods were introduced to provide backward compatibility for old interfaces ,so that they can have
      new methods without affecting existing code.
      or in other words we can say that without affecting implementation classes of interface if we want to add a new
      method inside interface that time we use default method.

Q.4 ) WHat is static method with respective of interfaces ?
ans : To define general utility methods inside an interface we are use static methods.



